          { "feature": "serum_osmolality_gt_320", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "profound_dehydration_altered_mental_status", "weight": 5 }
        ],
        "management": "Aggressive IV fluids (1-2L NS bolus, then 0.45% NS at 250-500ml/h). Insulin lower dose than DKA. Recheck osmolality. K replacement. Identify and treat precipitant (infection, stroke, MI). ICU admission."
      }
